<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Pitiful" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pitiful,</orth> 1) compassionate: <cit><quote>that p. rumour may report my flight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 3.2.130" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 2, 130</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>good ground, be p. and hurt me not,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.2" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 2</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 2, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.109" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.141" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.32" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.141" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.40" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 169</bibl>. With <emph>to</emph>: <cit><quote>be p. to my sons,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 8</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) moving compassion; <cit><quote>p. mischances,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 976" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 976</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>such p. dole,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.139" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 139</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the ballad is very p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.286" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 286</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.286" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 286</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 1, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.5.99" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 5, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.174" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 2, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.208" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 208</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.210" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 210</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 22</bibl>. With <emph>to</emph>: <cit><quote>p. to the eye,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 151</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) miserable, wretched, contemptible: <cit><quote>p. thrivers, in their gazing spent,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 125.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 125, 8</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I should be a p. lady,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 3, 56</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a p. bald crown,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.420" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 420</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.70" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.208" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 208</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 49</bibl>.
<lb />Adverbially: <cit><quote>how p. I deserve,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 2, 29</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>